&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;Policy type is a non-cancelable and guaranteed renewable contract&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;Coverage is portable (take it with you if you leave the company)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;Discounted 30% from ‘retail’ rates&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;Able to cover total compensation over and above the existing Group LTD plan&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;Since you pay the premiums, benefits would normally be considered non-taxable&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;','About This Policy',1411591870,30,0,0),(159,158,'about provider','&lt;div&gt;At Unum, we’re in the business of helping people through difficult times in their lives. Our financial protection benefits provide individuals and their families with the financial security they need to better cope with the loss of a loved one or the inability to work due to illness or injury.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;We offer a full array of benefits solutions (including education, enrollment services and valuable claim support) to meet the needs of both employers and their workers. And our award-winning absence management and vocational rehabilitation services help ease the disruption to both businesses and employers by enabling them to return to full capacity as soon as they are able.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;Unum at a glance:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ranks 272 on the Fortune 500&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Protects 20 million people worldwide&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Serves the needs of 175,000 businesses in the U.S. and U.K.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Providing benefits for a third of Fortune 500 companies&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;','About This Provider',1411591870,30,0,0),(152,158,'decline','Do you wish to decline this coverage?&amp;nbsp;&lt;div&gt;Please use the area below to let us know why you are declining.&lt;/div&gt;','Decline',1411591870,30,0,0),(153,158,'contact','&lt;br&gt;','Contact Us',1411591870,30,0,0),(151,158,'factsheet','&lt;font size=&quot;5&quot; color=&quot;#6494b4&quot;&gt;Here are the Facts:&lt;/font&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\n\n&lt;font face=&quot;helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif&quot; size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;\n\n\n&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;Worldwide, over one billion people live with some form of disability.\n  &lt;br&gt;\n&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;World Health Organization, http://www.who.int/features/factfiles/disability/facts/en/ 2014\n  &lt;br&gt;\n&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;More than 38 million Americans suffer disabling injuries each year.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n\n&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;National Safety Council, Injury Facts, 2011 edition.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n\n\n&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;Approximately 1 in 3 people will experience some kind of adult onset disability between the ages of 35 and 65.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;Society for Human Resource Management, Job Accommodation Network Conference, &quot;Plan B&quot; by Steven Nissen, August 2007.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;Almost 3 in 10 workers entering the work force today will become disabled before retirement.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;Social Security Administration, Fact Sheet, January 31, 2007.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n\n\n&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;Nearly one in five Americans will become disabled for a year or more before the age of 65.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n\n&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;Life and Health Insurance Foundation for Education (LIFE), &quot;Disability Insurance: Who Needs It?&quot; May 2007.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n\n&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;A Medical crisis contributes to half of all mortgage foreclosures.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;Get Sick, Get Out: The Medical Causes of Home Mortgage Foreclosures, Robertson, Egelhof &amp;amp; Hoke\n  &lt;br&gt;\n&lt;/p&gt;\n\n\n\n&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;Disability causes nearly 50% of all mortgage foreclosures, compared to 2% that are caused by loss of life.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n\n&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;WPLG, Miami, &quot;Disability Insurance Offers Vital Protection,&quot; July 31, 2007.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;Approximately one in three people will experience some kind of adult-onset disability between the ages of 35 and 65, such as arthritis, lupus, diabetes, spinal cord injuries, mental disorders, or MS.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;SHRM, Job Accommodation Network Conference &quot;&#39;Plan B&#39; Needed for Adult-Onset Disabilities Such as MS,&quot; speech by Steven Nissen, director of employment programs for the National Multiple Sclerosis Society, August 2007.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n\n&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;Since 2000, the number of disabled workers in America has increased by 35% while the financial health of many American workers has declined.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n\n&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;Council for Disability Awareness, &quot;Misinformation, Poor Planning Can Threaten Financial Security,&quot; March 7, 2007.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n\n&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;56 % of U.S. adults surveyed say they would not be able to pay their bills or meet expenses if they became disabled and could not work for a year or longer.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;National Association of Insurance Commissioners, &quot;Majority of Americans Unprepared for Financial Impact of Disability,&quot; February 28, 2007.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;A survey of American workers shows that nine out of 10 workers underestimate their chance of becoming disabled.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n\n&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Council for Disability Awareness, &quot;Most Workers Underestimate Chances, Impact of Disability, Survey Shows,&quot; March 7, 2007.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n\n&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;Most disabling injuries suffered by American workers occur off the job and are not covered by workers&#39; compensation.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n\n&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;National Safety Council, Injury Facts, 2005-2006 edition.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n\n&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;The average monthly Social Security Disability Insurance benefit is only $978.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n\n&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;Social Security Administration, Fact Sheet, January 31, 2007.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n\n\n&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;About two-thirds of initial applications are denied and the wait for appeals can take as long as three years.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n\n&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;The New York Times, &quot;Disability Cases Last Longer as Backlog Rises,&quot; by Erik Eckholm, December 10, 2007.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;!-- autocreated page --&gt;','Fact Sheet',1411591870,30,0,0),(170,160,'faq','[{\"question\":\"Whom should I call with questions? &nbsp;<br>\",\"answer\":\"<span style=\\\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-size: 12px;\\\">Please call Unum\\u2019s CVS Caremark Supplemental IDI Enrollment Line at 1-888-483-6447.&nbsp;</span><br>\",\"order\":0},{\"question\":\"What are the main advantages of applying for the coverage through this option rather than attempting to purchase it on my own? &nbsp;&nbsp;\",\"answer\":\"<div style=\\\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-size: 12px;\\\">Discounted Premium Rates because you are an employee of CVS Caremark. &nbsp;</div><div style=\\\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-size: 12px;\\\">Guaranteed standard issue* underwriting allows you to apply for the Supplemental Individual Disability Insurance (IDI) Program with no medical exam; however, you will be asked a few medical questions and benefits may be subject to a pre-existing condition limitation. &nbsp;</div><div style=\\\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-size: 12px;\\\">No medical exam is required if you apply now. &nbsp;</div><div style=\\\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-size: 12px;\\\">Convenient payroll deduction.</div>\",\"order\":1},{\"question\":\"How much coverage can I purchase?&nbsp;\",\"answer\":\"<span style=\\\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-size: 12px;\\\">This depends on your income level and any other disability coverage you may have in force.</span>\",\"order\":2},{\"question\":\"I already own individual insurance, can I still participate?&nbsp;\",\"answer\":\"<span style=\\\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-size: 12px;\\\">YES. A comparison of the Supplemental Individual Disability Insurance (IDI) Program with any existing coverage can be illustrated for you by calling 1-866-920-2670 for additional information.</span>\",\"order\":3},{\"question\":\"What happens if I terminate employment? &nbsp;\",\"answer\":\"<span style=\\\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-size: 12px;\\\">Your coverage is individually owned which means you take it with you if you leave the company. Your policy premium will not increase until age 65.</span>\",\"order\":4},{\"question\":\"If I use tobacco in any form will it affect my premium? &nbsp;&nbsp;\",\"answer\":\"<span style=\\\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-size: 12px;\\\">YES. Your personalized information provides premiums for both tobacco and non-tobacco use. If you are an occasional cigar smoker (less than two cigars per month) you should complete the form as a non-tobacco user. Please provide details of your cigar use after question 4.</span>\",\"order\":5},{\"question\":\"If I don\'t enroll now, can I participate in the future? &nbsp;\",\"answer\":\"<span style=\\\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-size: 12px;\\\">If you do not apply for coverage now, you may be required to provide full medical underwriting in the future if you choose to apply later.</span>\",\"order\":6},{\"question\":\"Can I discontinue coverage at any time? &nbsp;\",\"answer\":\"<span style=\\\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-size: 12px;\\\">YES. Premiums will be deducted from your pay each pay period. You may discontinue your participation in this program at any time by calling the Unum CVS Caremark Policy Services Line at 1-800-633-7490.</span>\",\"order\":7},{\"question\":\"Can Unum cancel my policy? &nbsp;\",\"answer\":\"<span style=\\\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-size: 12px;\\\">Your policy cannot be cancelled or modified before age 65 without your permission as long as you continue to pay your premiums when due.</span>\",\"order\":8},{\"question\":\"If I become disabled, do I still have to pay premiums? &nbsp;\",\"answer\":\"<span style=\\\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-size: 12px;\\\">NO. After 90 days of covered disability, all future premiums will be waived while you continue to receive benefits under the Supplemental Individual Disability Insurance (IDI) Program. Any premiums paid during the 90 days will be refunded.</span>\",\"order\":9},{\"question\":\"If I am receiving benefits under the Group LTD Plan, can I still receive benefits under the Supplemental Individual Disability Insurance (IDI) Program? &nbsp;\",\"answer\":\"<span style=\\\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-size: 12px;\\\">YES. Your Supplemental Individual Disability Insurance (IDI) Program monthly benefit will not be offset or reduced by benefits received under the Group LTD Plan.</span>\",\"order\":10},{\"question\":\"Is my Supplemental Individual Disability Insurance (IDI) Program benefit payment taxable? &nbsp;\",\"answer\":\"<span style=\\\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-size: 12px;\\\">Because you pay the premium for your &nbsp;Supplemental Individual Disability Insurance (IDI) Program coverage with \\\"after tax\\\" dollars, your benefit will be \\\"tax-free\\\", under current tax laws.</span>\",\"order\":11},{\"question\":\"Where do I need to send the completed application? &nbsp;\",\"answer\":\"<span style=\\\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-size: 12px;\\\">Please complete the application via the web and submit.</span>\",\"order\":12},{\"question\":\"When is my coverage effective? &nbsp;\",\"answer\":\"<span style=\\\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-size: 12px;\\\">If accepted, coverage will be effective the first of the month in which payroll deductions begin, if, for the period of time commencing 180 days prior to, and including, the date of the application, you have been continuously at work on a full-time basis performing all the duties of your occupation without limitation due to injury or sickness and have not been hospitalized or homebound or hospitalized due to an injury or sickness. &nbsp;</span>\",\"order\":13},{\"question\":\"When do payroll deductions begin? &nbsp;\",\"answer\":\"<span style=\\\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-size: 12px;\\\">Your payroll deductions will begin in November. Premiums are deducted one month in advance of the policy date.&nbsp;</span>\",\"order\":14}]','Frequently Asked Questions',1411673077,5,0,0),(171,160,'apply now','When you click the apply now button you will be transferred to the insurance carrier&#39;s website to complete the simplified enrollment process.&lt;!-- autocreated page --&gt;','Apply Now',1411673077,5,0,0),(172,160,'return from carrier','&lt;!-- autocreated page --&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot; color=&quot;#6494b4&quot;&gt;You application has been submitted successfully!&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;What to expect next...&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt