ipate in the future? \",\"answer\":\"If you do not apply for coverage now, you may be required to provide full medical underwriting in the future if you choose to apply later.\",\"order\":7},{\"question\":\"Can I discontinue coverage at any time? \",\"answer\":\"YES. Premiums will be deducted from your pay each pay period. You may discontinue your participation in this program at any time by calling the Unum CompanyName Policy Services Line at 800-633-7490.\",\"order\":8},{\"question\":\"Can Unum cancel my policy? \",\"answer\":\"Your policy cannot be cancelled or modified before age 65 without your permission as long as you continue to pay your premiums when due.\\n\",\"order\":9},{\"question\":\"If I become disabled, do I still have to pay premiums? \",\"answer\":\"NO. After 90 days of covered disability, all future premiums will be waived while you continue to receive benefits under the PolicyBranding. Any premiums paid during the 90 days will be refunded.\\n\",\"order\":10},{\"question\":\"Where do I need to send the completed application? \",\"answer\":\"Please complete the application via the web and submit.\\n\",\"order\":11},{\"question\":\"Is my PolicyBranding benefit payment taxable?\",\"answer\":\"Since you will be paying the premium with after-tax dollars, your benefit, if disabled, will be tax free.\\n\",\"order\":12},{\"question\":\"Where do I need to send the completed application?\",\"answer\":\"Where do I need to send the completed application?  Please complete the application via the web and submit.\",\"order\":13}]','Frequently Asked Questions',1414693535,320,0,0),(190,162,'faq','[{\"question\":\"What are the main advantages of applying for the coverage through this option rather than attempting to purchase it on my own? \",\"answer\":\"Discounted Premium Rates since you are an employee of  CompanyName.&nbsp;<div>Guaranteed standard issue* underwriting allows you to apply for the IDI Plan with no medical exam; however, you will be asked a few medi