 year.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#99ccff&quot; size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;National Safety Council, Injury Facts, 2011 edition.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;&gt;8.8 million disabled wage earners were receiving Social Security Disability (SSDI) benefits at the end of 2012.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#99ccff&quot; size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;U.S. Social Security Administration, Disabled Worker Beneficiary Data, December 2012&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;&gt;2.5 million disabled wage earners in their 20s, 30s, and 40s were receiving SSDI benefits at the end of 2012.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#99ccff&quot; size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;U.S. Social Security Administration, Disabled Worker Beneficiary Data, December 2012&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;&gt;Just over 1 in 4 of today&#39;s 20 year-olds will become disabled before they retire.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#99ccff&quot; size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;U.S. Social Security Administration, Fact Sheet February 7, 2013&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;&gt;65% of working Americans say they could not cover normal living expenses even for a year if their employment income was lost; 38% could not pay their bills for more than 3 months.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;