\":7},{\"question\":\"Can the carrier cancel my policy? \",\"answer\":\"Your policy cannot be cancelled or modified before age 67 without your permission as long as you continue to pay your premiums when due.\\n\",\"order\":8},{\"question\":\"If I become disabled, do I still have to pay premiums? \",\"answer\":\"NO. After 180 days of covered disability, all future premiums will be waived while you continue to receive benefits under the IDI plan. Any premiums paid during the 180 days will be refunded.\\n\",\"order\":9},{\"question\":\"Is my IDI benefit taxable?\",\"answer\":\"Since you will be paying the premium with after-tax dollars, your benefit, if disabled, will be tax free.\\n\",\"order\":10},{\"question\":\"Where do I need to send the completed application?\",\"answer\":\"Please complete the application via the web and submit.\",\"order\":11}]','Frequently Asked Questions',1431112657,30,0,0),(251,168,'factsheet','&lt;div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#6494b4&quot; size=&quot;5&quot;&gt;Facts about Disability:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#6494b4&quot; size=&quot;5&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;&gt;Worldwide, over one billion people live with some form of disability. &amp;nbsp;Rates of disability are increasing.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#99ccff&quot; size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;World Health Organization, http://www.who.int/features/factfiles/disability/facts/en/ 2014&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;&gt;More than 38 million Americans suffer disabling injuries each year.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#99ccff&quot; size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;National Safety Council, Injury Facts, 2011 edition.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;&gt;8.8 million disabled wage earners were receiving Social Security Disability (SSDI) benefits at the end of 2012.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#99ccff&quot; size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;U.S. Social Security Administration, Disabled Worker Beneficiary Data, December 2012&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;&gt;2.5 million disabled wage earners in their 20s, 30s, and 40s were receiving SSDI benefits at the end of 2012.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#99ccff&quot; size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;U.S. Social Security Administration, Disabled Worker Beneficiary Data, December 2012&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;&gt;Just over 1 in 4 of today&#39;s 20 year-olds will become disabled before they retire.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#99ccff&quot; size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;U.S. Social Security Administration, Fact Sheet February 7, 2013&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;&gt;65% of working Americans say they could not cover normal living expenses even for a year if their employment income was lost; 38% could not pay their bills for more than 3 months.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot; color=&quot;#99ccff&quot;&gt;Council for Disability Awareness, Disability Divide Consumer Disability Awareness Study, 2010&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- autocreated page