an><span style=\\\"font-size: 13px; font-family: helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif;\\\">policy with you at the same discounted rate if you were to change employers.&nbsp;</span><font face=\\\"helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size: 13px;\\\"><br></span></font></i></div><div style=\\\"font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 12px;\\\"><i><font face=\\\"helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size: 13px;\\\"><b>No Medical Exams -&nbsp;</b></span></font><span style=\\\"font-size: 13px; font-family: helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif;\\\">This Guaranteed Standard Issue coverage is applied for by answering a few simple questions</span></i></div><div style=\\\"font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 12px;\\\"><i><span style=\\\"font-size: 13px; font-family: helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif;\\\"><b>Discounted Rates -</b>&nbsp;</span><span style=\\\"font-size: 13px; font-family: helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif;\\\">25% premium reduction</span></i></div><div style=\\\"font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 12px;\\\"><i><font face=\\\"helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size: 13px;\\\"><b>Fixed Premiums &amp; Non-cancellable -</b>&nbsp;</span></font><span style=\\\"font-size: 13px; font-family: helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif;\\\">This benefit is non-cancellable, guaranteed renewable coverage to age 67,&nbsp;</span><span style=\\\"font-size: 13px; font-family: helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif;\\\">which means as long as you continue to pay your premiums, only you can cancel your policy. Your rates are also guaranteed&nbsp;</span><span style=\\\"font-size: 13px; font-family: helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif;\\\">never to increase until the expiration date.&nbsp;</span></i></div><div style=\\\"font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 12px;\\\"><i><font face=\\\"helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size: 13px;\\\"><b>Tax-free Benefits -</b>&nbsp;</span></font><span style=\\\"font-size: 13px; font-family: helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif;\\\">Since you pay the premiums, you are not subject to taxes.*</span></i></div><div style=\\\"font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 12px;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size: 13px; font-family: helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif;\\\"><i><br></i></span></div><div style=\\\"font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 12px;\\\"><font face=\\\"helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size: 13px;\\\"><i>*This illustration is offered for the purposes of education and information only and should not be considered tax or legal advice. For information on your specific situation,&nbsp;</i></span></font><span style=\\\"font-size: 13px; font-family: helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif;\\\"><i>please consult your legal or tax advisor.</i>&nbsp;</span></div>\",\"order\":0},{\"question\":\"Who pays for this benefit? \",\"answer\":\"You pay for the cost of this coverage through payroll deduction.\\n\",\"order\":1},{\"question\":\"How much coverage can I purchase? \",\"answer\":\"This depends on your income level and any other disability coverage you may have in force.\\n\",\"order\":2},{\"question\":\"I already own individual insurance, can I still participate? \",\"answer\":\"YES. A comparison of the IDI plan with any existing coverage can be illustrated for you by calling (888) 986-6677 for additional information.\\n\",\"order\":3},{\"question\":\"What happens if I terminate employment? \",\"answer\":\"Your coverage is individually owned which means you take it with you if you leave the company. Your policy premium will not increase for the life of the policy or until age 67.\",\"order\":4},{\"question\":\"If I use tobacco in any form will it affect my premium?\",\"answer\":\"YES. Your personalized information provides premiums for both tobacco and non-tobacco use. Please provide details (type and usage) of your tobacco use during the application process.\",\"order\":5},{\"question\":\"If I don\'t enroll now, can I participate in the future? \",\"answer\":\"If you do not apply for coverage now, you may be required to provide full medical underwriting in the future if you choose to apply later.\",\"order\":6},{\"question\":\"Can I discontinue coverage at any time? \",\"answer\":\"YES. Premiums will be deducted from your pay each pay period. You may discontinue your participation in this program at any time by calling The Todd Org.\",\"order\":7},{\"question\":\"Can the carrier cancel my policy? \",\"answer\":\"Your policy cannot be cancelled or modified before age 67 without your permission as long as you continue to pay your premiums when due.\\n\",\"order\":8},{\"question\":\"If I become disabled, do I still have to pay premiums? \",\"answer\":\"NO. After 180 days of covered disability, all future premiums will be waived while you continue to receive benefits under the IDI plan. Any premiums paid during the 180 days will be refunded.\\n\",\"order\":9},{\"question\":\"Is my IDI benefit taxable?\",\"answer\":\"Since you will be paying the premium with after-tax dollars, your benefit, if disabled, will be tax free.\\n\",\"order\":10},{\"question\":\"Where do I need to send the completed application?\",\"answer\":\"Please complete the application via the web and submit.\",\"order\":11}]','Frequently Asked Questions',1435755913,30,0,0),(311,174,'factsheet','&lt;div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#6494b4&quot; size=&quot;5&quot;&gt;Facts about Disability:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#6494b4&quot; size=&quot;5&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;&gt;Worldwide, over one billion people live with some form of disability. &amp;nbsp;Rates of disability are increasing.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#99ccff&quot; size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;World Health Organization, http://www.who.int/features/factfiles/disability/facts/en/ 2014&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;&gt;More than 38 million Americans suffer disabling injuries each year.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#99ccff&quot; size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;National Safety Council, Injury Facts, 2011 edition.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;&gt;8.8 million disabled wage earners were receiving Social Security Disability (SSDI) benefits at the end of 2012.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#99ccff&quot; size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;U.S. Social Security Administration, Disabled Worker Beneficiary Data, December 2012&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;&gt;2.5 million disabled wage earners in their 20s, 30s, and 40s were receiving SSDI benefits at the end of 2012.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#99ccff&quot; size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;U.S. Social Security Administration, Disabled Worker Beneficiary Data, December 2012&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;&gt;Just over 1 in 4 of today&#39;s 20 year-olds will become disabled before they retire.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#99ccff&quot; size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;U.S. Social Security Administration, Fact Sheet February 7, 2013&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;&