/o:p&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt&quot;&gt;A.M. Best\nCompany - A++&amp;nbsp; (Superior - highest of 15\nratings)&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt&quot;&gt;Fitch - AA+ &amp;nbsp;(Very Strong - 2nd highest of 21 ratings)&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt&quot;&gt;Moody&#39;s Investors\nService - Aa2 (Excellent - 3rd highest of 21 ratings)&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt&quot;&gt;Standard\n&amp;amp; Poor’s - AA+ (Very Strong - 2nd highest of 22 ratings)&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt&quot;&gt;Comdex\nRanking: 98&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;!-- autocreated page --&gt;','About This Provider',1435755913,30,0,0),(320,175,'faq','[{\"question\":\"Whom should I call with questions? \",\"answer\":\"<span style=\\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\\\">Please call the Enrollment Line at </span><font face=\\\"helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size: 13px;\\\">800.262.7701</span></font><font face=\\\"helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size: 13px;\\\">.</span></font>\",\"order\":0},{\"question\":\"What are the main advantages of applying for the coverage through this option rather than attempting to purchase it on my own? \",\"answer\":\"Discounted Premium Rates since you are an employee of &nbsp;Carolinas HealthCare System.&nbsp;<div>Portable coverage in the form of an individually-owned insurance policy<br><div>Guaranteed standard issue* underwriting allows you to apply for the Supplemental IDI Plan with no medical exam; however, you will be asked a few medical questions and benefits may be subject to a pre-existing condition limitation.&nbsp; </div><div>No medical exam is required if you apply now.</div></div>\",\"order\":1},{\"question\":\"Who pays for this benefit? \",\"answer\":\"You pay for the cost of this coverage, with discounted rates made available through this offering.\",\"order\":2},{\"question\":\"How much coverage can I purchase? \",\"answer\":\"This depends on your income level and any other disability coverage you may have in force.\\n\",\"order\":3},{\"question\":\"I already own individual insurance, can I still participate? \",\"answer\":\"YES. A comparison of the Supplemental IDI plan with any existing coverage can be illustrated for you by calling 800.262.7701&nbsp;for additional information.\\n\",\"order\":4},{\"question\":\"What happens if I terminate employment? \",\"answer\":\"Your coverage is individually owned which means you take it with you if you leave the company. Your policy premium will not increase until age 65.\",\"order\":5},{\"question\":\"If I use tobacco in any form will it affect my premium?\",\"answer\":\"YES. Your personalized information provides premiums for both tobacco and non-tobacco use. Please provide details (type and usage) of your tobacco use on the electronic application.\",\"order\":6},{\"question\":\"If I don\'t enroll now, can I participate in the future? \",\"answer\":\"If you do not apply for coverage now, you may be required to provide full medical underwriting in the future if you choose to apply later.\",\"order\":7},{\"question\":\"Can I discontinue coverage at any time? \",\"answer\":\"YES. Premiums will be deducted from your pay each pay period. You may discontinue your participation in this program at any time by calling 800.262.7701.\",\"order\":8},{\"question\":\"Can Unum cancel my policy? \",\"answer\":\"Your policy cannot be cancelled or modified before age 65 without your permission as long as you continue to pay your premiums when due.\\n\",\"order\":9},{\"question\":\"If I become disabled, do I still have to pay premiums? \",\"answer\":\"NO. After 90 days of covered disability, all future premiums will be waived while you continue to receive benefits under the Supplemental IDI plan. Any premiums paid during the 90 days will be refunded.\\n\",\"order\":10},{\"question\":\"Where do I need to send the completed application? \",\"answer\":\"Please complete the application via the web and submit.\\n\",\"order\":11},{\"question\":\"Is my Supplemental IDI benefit payment taxable?\",\"answer\":\"Since you will be paying the premium with after-tax dollars, your benefit, if disabled, will be tax free.\\n\",\"order\":12}]','Frequently Asked Questions',1436364302,30,0,0),(321,175,'factsheet','&lt;div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#6494b4&quot; size=&quot;5&quot;&gt;Facts about Disability:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#6494b4&quot; size=&quot;5&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;&gt;Worldwide, over one billion people live with some form of disability. &amp;nbsp;Rates of disability are increasing.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#99ccff&quot; size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;World Health Organization, http://www.who.int/features/factfiles/disability/facts/en/ 2014&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;&gt;More than 38 million Americans suffer disabling injuries each year.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#99ccff&quot; size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;National Safety Council, Injury Facts, 2011 edition.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;&gt;8.8 million disabled wage earners were receiving Social Security Disability (SSDI) benefits at the end of 2012.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#99ccff&quot; size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;U.S. Social Security Administration, Disabled Worker Beneficiary Data, December 2012&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;&gt;2.5 million disabled wage earners in their 20s, 30s, and 40s were receiving SSDI benefits at the end of 2012.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#99ccff&quot; size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;U.S. Social Security Administration, Disabled Worker Beneficiary Data, December 2012&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;&gt;Just over 1 in 4 of today&#39;s 20 year-olds will become disabled before they retire.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#99ccff&quot; size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;U.S. Social Security Administration, Fact Sheet February 7, 2013&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;&gt;65%\n of working Americans say they could not cover normal living expenses \neven for a year if their employment income was lost; 38% could not pay \ntheir bills for more than 3 months.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#99ccff&quot; size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;Council for Disability Awareness, Disability Divide Consumer Disability Awareness Study, 2010&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- autocreated page --&gt;','Fact Sheet',1436364302,30,0,0),(322,175,'decline','Do you wish to decline this coverage?&amp;nbsp;&lt;div&gt;Pleas