\\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-size: 12px;\\\">This depends on your income level and any other disability coverage you may have in force.</span>\",\"order\":1},{\"question\":\"I already own individual insurance, can I still participate?&nbsp;\",\"answer\":\"<span style=\\\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-size: 12px;\\\">YES. A comparison of the Supplemental Individual Disability Insurance (IDI) Program with any existing coverage can be illustrated for you by calling </span><span style=\\\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-size: 12px;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-size: 12px;\\\">800 895-3389</span> for additional information.</span>\",\"order\":2},{\"question\":\"What happens if I terminate employment? &nbsp;\",\"answer\":\"<span style=\\\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-size: 12px;\\\">Your coverage is individually owned which means you take it with you if you leave the company. Your policy premium will not increase until age 65.</span>\",\"order\":3},{\"question\":\"If I use tobacco in any form will it affect my premium? &nbsp;&nbsp;\",\"answer\":\"<span style=\\\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-size: 12px;\\\">YES. Your personalized information provides premiums for both tobacco and non-tobacco use. If you are an occasional cigar smoker (one cigar or less per month) you should complete the form as a non-tobacco user. Please provide details of your cigar use after question 4.</span>\",\"order\":4},{\"question\":\"If I don\'t enroll now, can I participate in the future? &nbsp;\",\"answer\":\"<span style=\\\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-size: 12px;\\\">If you do not apply for coverage now, you may be required to provide full medical underwriting in the future if you choose to apply later.</span>\",\"order\":5},{\"question\":\"Can I discontinue coverage at any time? &nbsp;\",\"answer\":\"<span style=\\\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-size: 12px;\\\">YES. Premiums will be deducted from your pay each pay period. You may discontinue your participation in this program at any time by calling the Unum CVS Health Policy Services Line at 1-800-633-7490.</span>\",\"order\":6},{\"question\":\"Can Unum cancel my policy? &nbsp;\",\"answer\":\"<span style=\\\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-size: 12px;\\\">Your policy cannot be cancelled or modified before age 65 without your permission as long as you continue to pay your premiums when due.</span>\",\"order\":7},{\"question\":\"If I become disabled, do I still have to pay premiums? &nbsp;\",\"answer\":\"<span style=\\\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-size: 12px;\\\">NO. After 90 days of covered disability, all future premiums will be waived while you continue to receive benefits under the Supplemental Individual Disability Insurance (IDI) Program. Any premiums paid during the 90 days will be refunded.</span>\",\"order\":8},{\"question\":\"If I am receiving benefits under the Group LTD Plan, can I still receive benefits under the Supplemental Individual Disability Insurance (IDI) Program? &nbsp;\",\"answer\":\"<span style=\\\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-size: 12px;\\\">YES. Your Supplemental Individual Disability Insurance (IDI) Program monthly benefit will not be offset or reduced by benefits received under the Group LTD Plan.</span>\",\"order\":9},{\"question\":\"Is my Supplemental Individual Disability Insurance (IDI) Program benefit payment taxable? &nbsp;\",\"answer\":\"<span style=\\\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-size: 12px;\\\">Because you pay the premium for your Supplemental Individual Disability Insurance (IDI) Program coverage with \\\"after tax\\\" dollars, your benefit will be \\\"tax-free\\\", under current tax laws.</span>\",\"order\":10},{\"question\":\"Where do I need to send the completed application? &nbsp;\",\"answer\":\"<span style=\\\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-size: 12px;\\\">Please complete the application via the web and submit.</span>\",\"order\":11},{\"question\":\"When is my coverage effective? &nbsp;\",\"answer\":\"<span style=\\\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-size: 12px;\\\">If accepted, coverage will be effective the first of the month in which payroll deductions begin, if, for the period of time commencing 180 days prior to, and including, the date of the application, you have been continuously at work on a full-time basis performing all the duties of your occupation without limitation due to injury or sickness and have not been hospitalized or homebound or hospitalized due to an injury or sickness. &nbsp;</span>\",\"order\":12},{\"question\":\"When do payroll deductions begin? &nbsp;\",\"answer\":\"<span style=\\\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-size: 12px;\\\">Your payroll deductions will begin in October. Premiums are deducted one month in advance of the policy date.&nbsp;</span>\",\"order\":13}]','Frequently Asked Questions',1439471713,30,0,0),(354,178,'apply now','When you click the apply now button you will be transferred to the insurance carrier&#39;s website to complete the simplified enrollment process.&lt;!-- autocreated page --&gt;','Apply Now',1439471713,30,0,0),(355,178,'return from carrier','&lt;!-- autocreated page --&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#6494b4&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;You application has been submitted successfully!&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;&quot;&gt;What to expect next...&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;&quot;&gt;If you have applied for c