 in this plan, you will be required to provide proof of good health at that time.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;&quot;&gt;Please contact us at (888) 483-6447 with questions.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;','Application Successfully Submitted',1439471713,30,0,0),(416,184,'error','&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;&gt;There was an error submitting your application.&amp;nbsp; Please contact us at\n&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#6494b4&quot; size=&quot;5&quot;&gt;(888) 640-8470&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br&gt;','Error Submitting Application',1442439175,30,0,0),(417,184,'logout','You have been successfully logged out.','Logged Out',1442439175,30,0,0),(418,184,'about policy','&lt;div&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif&quot; size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;Individual Disability Insurance (IDI) programs offer individually owned insurance policies offered in a multi-life setting. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif&quot; size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: small;&quot;&gt;IDI coverage is offered through a simplified underwriting process (Guaranteed Standard Issue)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: small;&quot;&gt;Level premium structure to your age 65&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: small;&quot;&gt;Policy type is a non-cancelable and guaranteed renewable contract&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: small;&quot;&gt;Coverage is portable (take it with you if you leave the company)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: small;&quot;&gt;Discounted 30% from ‘retail’ rates&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: small;&quot;&gt;Able to cover total compensation over and above the existing Group LTD plan&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: small;&quot;&gt;Since you pay the premiums, benefits would not generally be considered non-taxable.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- autocreated page --&gt;','About This Policy',1442439175,30,0,0),(419,184,'about provider','&lt;div&gt;At Unum, we’re in the business of helping people through difficult times in their lives. Our financial protection benefits provide individuals and their families with the financial security they need to better cope with the loss of a loved one or the inability to work due to illness or injury.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;We offer a full array of benefits solutions (including education, enrollment services and valuable claim support) to meet the needs of both employers and their workers. And our award-winning absence management and vocational rehabilitation services help ease the disruption to both businesses and employers by enabling them to return to full capacity as soon as they are able.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;Unum at a glance:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ranks 272 on the Fortune 500&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Protects 20 million people worldwide&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Serves the needs of 175,000 businesses in the U.S. and U.K.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Providing benefits for a third of Fortune 500 companies&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- autocreated page --&gt;','About This Provider',1442439175,30,0,0),(421,185,'factsheet','&lt;div&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;5&quot; color=&quot;#6494b4&quot;&gt;Here are the Facts:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot; face=&quot;helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;Worldwide, over one billion people live with some form of disability.&amp;nbsp; Rates of disability are increasing.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;World Health Organization, http://www.who.int/features/factfiles/disability/facts/en/ 2014&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;More than 38 million Americans suffer disabling injuries each year.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;National Safety Council, Injury Facts, 2011 edition.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;Approximately 1 in 3 people will experience some kind of adult onset disability between the ages of 35 and 65.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;Society for Human Resource Management, Job Accommodation Network Conference, &quot;Plan B&quot; by Steven Nissen, August 2007.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;Almost 3 in 10 workers entering the work force today will become disabled before retirement.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;Social Security Administration, Fact Sheet, January 31, 2007.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot; face=&quot;helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;Nearly one in five Americans will become disabled for a year or more before the age of 65.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;Life and Health Insurance Foundation for Education (LIFE), &quot;Disability Insurance: Who Needs It?&quot; May 2007.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;A Medical crisis contributes to half of all mortgage foreclosures.  &lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;Get Sick, Get Out: The Medical Causes of Home Mortgage Foreclosures, Robertson, Egelhof &amp;amp; Hoke&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;Disability causes nearly 50% of all mortgage foreclosures, compared to 2% that are caused by loss of life.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;WPLG, Miami, &quot;Disability Insurance Offers Vital Protection,&quot; July 31, 2007.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;Approximately one in three people will experience some kind of adult-onset disability between the ages of 35 and 65, such as arthritis, lupus, diabetes, spinal cord injuries, mental disorders, or MS.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;SHRM, Job Accommodation Network Conference &quot;&#39;Plan B&#39; Needed for Adult-Onset Disabilities Such as MS,&quot; speech by Steven Nissen, director of employment programs for the National Multiple Sclerosis Society, August 2007.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot; face=&quot;helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;Since 2000, the number of disabled workers in America has increased by 35% while the financial health of many American workers has declined.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;Council for Disability Awareness, &quot;Misinformation, Poor Planning Can Threaten Financial Security,&quot; March 7, 2007.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot; face=&quot;helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;56 % of U.S. adults surveyed say they would not be able to pay their bills or meet expenses if they became disabled and could not work for a year or longer.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;National Association of Insurance Commissioners, &quot;Majority of Americans Unprepared for Financial Impact of Disability,&quot; February 28, 2007.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot; face=&quot;helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;A survey of American workers shows that nine out of 10 workers underestimate their chance of becoming disabled.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Council for Disability Awareness, &quot;Most Workers Underestimate Chances, Impact of Disability, Survey Shows,&quot; March 7, 2007.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot; face=&quot;helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;Most disabling injuries suffered by American workers occur off the job and are not covered by workers&#39; compensation.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;National Safety Council, Injury Facts, 2005-2006 edition.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot; face=&quot;helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;The average monthly Social Security Disability Insurance benefit is only $978.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;Social Security Administration, Fact Sheet, January 31, 2007.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot; face=&quot;helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;About two-thirds of initial applications are denied and the wait for appeals can take as long as three years.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;The New York Times, &quot;Disability Cases Last Longer as Backlog Rises,&quot; by Erik Eckholm, December 10, 2007.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- autocreated page --&gt;','Fact Sheet',1442952869,30,0,0),(422,185,'decline','Do you wish to decline this coverage?&amp;nbsp;&lt;div&gt;Please use the area below to let us know why you are declining.&lt;/div&gt;','Decline',1442952869,30,0,0),(423,185,'contact','&lt;br&gt;','Contact Us',1442952869,30,0,0),(424,185,'apply now','When you click the apply now button you will be transferred to the insurance carrier&#39;s website to complete the simplified enrollment process.&lt;!-- autocreated page --&gt;','Apply Now',1442952869,30,0,0),(425,185,'return from carrier','&lt;!-- autocreated page --&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#6494b4&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;You application has been submitted successfully!&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;What to expect next...&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;If you have applied for coverage:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Thank you for applying. Your application is currently being reviewed. &amp;nbsp;If we have any questions about your application, we will contact you.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Once your application is approved:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;A policy will be mailed to your home in January. &amp;nbsp;Payroll deductions will begin in December.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;If your application is not approved:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;A letter will be sent your home explaining why it was not approved and your rights to appeal that decision.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;If you have declined the opportunity to participate in the Supplemental IDI plan. No further action is necessary. If you later decide to participate in this plan, you will be required to provide proof of good health at that time.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Please contact Dan Wisted in Atlanta toll-free at (888) 640-8470 or Don Hurwitz in Nashville at (615) 742-8712 or (800) 289-7724 with questions.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;','Application Successfully Submitted',1442952869,30,0,0),(426,185,'error','&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;&gt;There was an error submitting your application.&amp;nbsp; Please contact us at\n&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#6494b4&quot; size=&quot;5&quot;&gt;(888) 640-8470&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br&gt;','Error Submitting Application',1442952869,30,0,0),(427,185,'logout','You have been successfully logged out.','Logged Out',1442952869,30,0,0),(428,185,'about policy','&lt;div&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif&quot; size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;Individual Disability Insurance (IDI) programs offer individually owned insurance policies offered in a multi-life setting. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif&quot; size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: small;&quot;&gt;IDI coverage is offered through a simplified underwriting process (Guaranteed Standard Issue)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: small;&quot;&gt;Level premium structure to your age 65&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: small;&quot;&gt;Policy type is a non-cancelable and guaranteed renewable contract&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: small;&quot;&gt;Coverage is portable (take it with you if you leave the company)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: small;&quot;&gt;Discounted 30% from ‘retail’ rates&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: small;&quot;&gt;Able to cover total compensation over and above the existing Group LTD plan&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: small;&quot;&gt;Since you pay the premiums, benefits would not generally be considered non-taxable.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- autocreated page --&gt;','About This Policy',1442952869,30,0,0),(429,185,'about provider','&lt;div&gt;At Unum, we’re in the business of helping people through difficult times in their lives. Our financial protection benefits provide individuals and their families with the financial security they need to better cope with the loss of a loved one or the inability to work due to illness or injury.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;We offer a full array of benefits solutions (including education, enrollment services and valuable claim support) to meet the needs of both employers and their workers. And our award-winning absence management and vocational rehabilitation services help ease the disruption to both businesses and employers by enabling them to return to full capacity as soon as they are able.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;Unum at a glance:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ranks 272 on the Fortune 500&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Protects 20 million people worldwide&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Serves the needs of 175,000 businesses in the U.S. and U.K.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Providing benefits for a third of Fortune 500 companies&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- autocreated page --&gt;','About This Provider',1442952869,30,0,0),(430,186,'faq','[{\"question\":\"Whom should I call with questions? \",\"answer\":\"Please call Dan Wisted in Atlanta toll-free at (888) 640-8470 or Don Hurwitz in Nashville at (615) 742-8712 or (800) 289-7724.\",\"order\":0},{\"question\":\"What are the main advantages of applying for the coverage through this option rather than attempting to purchase it on my own? \",\"answer\":\"Discounted Premium Rates since you are an employee of  LifePoint Hospitals.&nbsp;<div><br></div><div>Guaranteed standard issue* underwriting allows you to apply for the Supplemental Individual Disability Insurance (IDI) Plan with no medical exam; however, you will be asked a few medical questions and benefits may be subject to a pre-existing condition limitation.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>Convenient payroll deduction.</div>\",\"order\":1},{\"question\":\"Who pays for this benefit? \",\"answer\":\"You pay for the cost of this coverage through payroll deduction.\\n\",\"order\":2},{\"question\":\"How much coverage can I purchase? \",\"answer\":\"This depends on your income level and any other disability coverage you may have in force.\\n\",\"order\":3},{\"question\":\"I already own individual insurance, can I still participate? \",\"answer\":\"YES. A comparison of the Supplemental IDI plan with any existing coverage can be illustrated for you by calling Dan Wisted in Atlanta toll-free at (888) 640-8470 or Don Hurwitz in Nashville at (615) 742-8712 or (800) 289-7724 for additional information.\\n\",\"order\":4},{\"question\":\"What happens if I terminate employment? \",\"answer\":\"Your coverage is individually owned which means you take it with you if you leave the company. Your policy premium will not increase until age 65.\",\"order\":5},{\"question\":\"If I use tobacco in any form will it affect my premium?\",\"answer\":\"YES. Your personalized information provides premiums for both tobacco and non-tobacco use. Please provide details (type and usage) of your tobacco use on the electronic application.\",\"order\":6},{\"question\":\"If I don\'t enroll now, can I participate in the future? \",\"answer\":\"If you do not apply for coverage now, you may be required to provide full medical underwriting in the future if you choose to apply later.\",\"order\":7},{\"question\":\"Can I discontinue coverage at any time? \",\"answer\":\"YES. Premiums will be deducted from your pay each pay period. You may discontinue your participation in this program at any time by calling the Unum Policy Services Line at 800-633-7490.\",\"order\":8},{\"question\":\"Can Unum cancel my policy? \",\"answer\":\"Your policy cannot be cancelled or modified before age 65 without your permission as long as you continue to pay your premiums when due.\\n\",\"order\":9},{\"question\":\"If I become disabled, do I still have to pay premiums? \",\"answer\":\"NO. After 90 days of covered disability, all future premiums will be waived while you continue to receive benefits under the Supplemental IDI plan. Any premiums paid during the 90 days will be refunded.\\n\",\"order\":10},{\"question\":\"Where do I need to send the completed application? \",\"answer\":\"Please complete the application via the web and submit.\\n\",\"order\":11},{\"question\":\"Is my IDI benefit taxable?\",\"answer\":\"Since you will be paying the premium with after-tax dollars, your benefit, if disabled, will be tax free.\\n\",\"order\":12}]','Frequently Asked Questions',1443029781,30,0,0),(440,187,'faq','[{\"question\":\"<b><span style=\\\"font-size:10.0pt;line-height:115%;\\nfont-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-font-family:\\nCalibri;mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;\\nmso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;color:#00B0F0;mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:\\nEN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA\\\">What is the Voluntary Disability Income benefit\\nprogram?<span class=\\\"apple-converted-space\\\">&nbsp;</span></span></b><br>\",\"answer\":\"<i><span style=\\\"font-size: 10pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\\\">Voluntary Disability Income will enable you to\\nsupplement your employer provided group long term disability (\\u201cLTD\\u201d) coverage\\nwith additional benefits from an individual disability income policy, at\\ndiscounted premium rates. The coverage helps protect your earnings by paying\\nyou monthly benefits in the event you are disabled and unable to work due to\\nillness or injury.</span></i><br>\",\"order\":0},{\"question\":\"<b><span style=\\\"font-size:10.0pt;line-height:115%;\\nfont-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-font-family:\\nCalibri;mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;\\nmso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;color:#00B0F0;mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:\\nEN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA\\\">How is the Voluntary Disability Income benefit\\nprogram different from the coverage I already have under my employer\\u2019s group\\nLTD plan?</span></b>\",\"answer\":\"<i><span style=\\\"font-size: 10pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\\\">The individual disability income coverage\\noffered through the Voluntary Disability Income program is designed in part to\\nprotect your incentive compensation as well as an additional portion of your\\nbase salary, while most group LTD plans do not.</span></i>\",\"order\":1},{\"question\":\"<b><span style=\\\"font-size:10.0pt;line-height:115%;\\nfont-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-font-family:\\nCalibri;mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;\\nmso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;color:#00B0F0;mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:\\nEN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA\\\">Is enrollment in the Voluntary Disability Income\\nbenefit program mandatory?&nbsp;</span></b>\",\"answer\":\"<i><span style=\\\"font-size: 10pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\\\">No, participation in this program is not\\nmandatory. However, if you have determined that additional long-term disability\\nincome coverage is an important component of your total insurance package, the\\nVoluntary Disability Income program\\u2019s individual disability income policy is\\nparticularly worth considering because it can be secured with limited\\nunderwriting. Many voluntary benefit programs require enrollees to pass a\\nmedical exam before coverage is provided, but that is not required by this\\nprogram</span></i><span style=\\\"font-size: 10pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\\\">.</span>\",\"order\":2},{\"question\":\"<b><span style=\\\"font-size:10.0pt;line-height:115%;\\nfont-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-font-family:\\nCalibri;mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;\\nmso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;color:#00B0F0;mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:\\nEN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA\\\">What are the main advantages of acquiring the\\nindividual disability income coverage through this program rather than\\nattempting to purchase it from an outside source?<span class=\\\"apple-converted-space\\\">&nbsp;</span></span></b>\",\"answer\":\"<i><span style=\\\"font-size: 10pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\\\">First premiums will be discounted due to a\\ndiscount negotiated with your employer. If you have been actively working for\\nthe 90 days prior to and including the date of application, you may enroll\\nregardless of the status of your health. You must also be working full time at\\nleast 30 hours per week on the effective date of the policy for coverage to be\\neffective. Please note that if you have been previously eligible and opted not\\nto apply, or you are applying for benefits in excess of the guaranteed issue\\noffer of up to $10,000 per month, a medical examination and/or comprehensive\\nmedical history will usually be needed to satisfy evidence of insurability\\nrequirements. Your medical history and/or medical examination results may cause\\nyour new policy to be rated, modified or your application to be declined.</span></i>\",\"order\":3},{\"question\":\"<b><span style=\\\"font-size:10.0pt;line-height:115%;\\nfont-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-font-family:\\nCalibri;mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;\\nmso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;color:#00B0F0;mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:\\nEN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA\\\">Why is the guaranteed issue feature important?&nbsp;</span></b>\",\"answer\":\"<i><span style=\\\"font-size: 10pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\\\">The guaranteed issue component of this program\\nmeans you can enroll quickly with limited medical underwriting and without a\\nmedical examination.</span></i>\",\"order\":4},{\"question\":\"<b><span style=\\\"font-size:10.0pt;line-height:115%;\\nfont-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-font-family:\\nCalibri;mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;\\nmso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;color:#00B0F0;mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:\\nEN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA\\\">What is the criteria to be eligible for a\\nguaranteed issue policy?&nbsp;<span class=\\\"apple-converted-space\\\">&nbsp;</span></span></b>\",\"answer\":\"<i><span style=\\\"font-size: 10pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\\\">To be eligible for a guaranteed issue policy,\\nyou must be actively at work for the 90 days prior to and including the date\\nyou complete the application and on the effective date of the policy.</span></i>\",\"order\":5},{\"question\":\"<b><span style=\\\"font-size:10.0pt;line-height:115%;\\nfont-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-font-family:\\nCalibri;mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;\\nmso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;color:#00B0F0;mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:\\nEN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA\\\">What happens if I do not apply for the coverage\\nthis year, but decide I want it next year? Can I still buy it without providing\\nmedical evidence of good health?&nbsp;<span class=\\\"apple-converted-space\\\">&nbsp;</span></span></b>\",\"answer\":\"<i><span style=\\\"font-size: 10pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\\\">To qualify a guaranteed standard issue policy,\\nyou must apply during your initial enrollment period. To obtain coverage in the\\nfuture, if you don\\u2019t apply this year, proof of good health is usually required.\\nYou may need to answer medical questions and/or have a medical examination.</span></i>\",\"order\":6},{\"question\":\"<b><span style=\\\"font-size:10.0pt;line-height:115%;\\nfont-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-font-family:\\nCalibri;mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;\\nmso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;color:#00B0F0;mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:\\nEN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA\\\">I already own individual disability insurance.\\nCan I still participate?&nbsp;<span class=\\\"apple-converted-space\\\">&nbsp;</span></span></b>\",\"answer\":\"<i><span style=\\\"font-size: 10pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\\\">Even if you own an individual disability income\\ninsurance policy not associated with your employer, you may still be able to\\nparticipate in the program. However the amount of the total amount of your\\nbenefit through this program may be reduced by the individual coverage you own;\\nfor many who own their own coverage, maintaining that coverage and forgoing\\nthis program may make the most sense. For more detailed information and to see\\nif you qualify for additional coverage, call your personal Financial Advisor.</span></i>\",\"order\":7},{\"question\":\"<b><span style=\\\"font-size:10.0pt;line-height:115%;\\nfont-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-font-family:\\nCalibri;mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;\\nmso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;color:#00B0F0;mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:\\nEN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA\\\">How is my Voluntary Disability Income benefit\\ncalculated?&nbsp;<span class=\\\"apple-converted-space\\\">&nbsp;</span></span></b>\",\"answer\":\"<i><span style=\\\"font-size: 10pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\\\">The benefit under the individual disability\\nincome policy is based on: 75 percent of your total compensation (current base\\nsalary plus an average of 2 years of paid incentive compensation. Projected\\nincentive compensation may also be used with MetLife prior approval) less your\\ncurrent group LTD and personal individual disability coverage, to a monthly\\nmaximum benefit of $10,000. If you did not yet receive your incentive\\ncompensation during this calendar year, 75 percent of your target or projected\\nincentive compensation may be used to determine your insurable incentive\\ncompensation.</span></i>\",\"order\":8},{\"question\":\"<b><span style=\\\"font-size:10.0pt;line-height:115%;\\nfont-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-font-family:\\nCalibri;mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;\\nmso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;color:#00B0F0;mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:\\nEN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA\\\">If my compensation increases in the future, can\\nI purchase additional coverage?&nbsp;<span class=\\\"apple-converted-space\\\">&nbsp;</span></span></b>\",\"answer\":\"<i><span style=\\\"font-size: 10pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\\\">If you apply for the maximum available benefits\\nduring the initial enrollment period as your compensation increases, you may be\\nable to increase your individual disability income policy benefit without a\\nmedical examination. You may do so as long as:&nbsp;</span></i><div><p style=\\\"margin-left:27.35pt\\\"><i><span style=\\\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\\\">\\u2022 You are actively at\\nwork as an employee of the employer offering this program <o:p></o:p></span></i></p>\\n\\n<p style=\\\"margin-left:27.35pt\\\"><i><span style=\\\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\\\">\\u2022 The employer and\\nMetLife continue to offer this program <o:p></o:p></span></i></p>\\n\\n<p style=\\