font-size: 10pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\\\">Yes, your premiums will be higher. If you stop\\nusing tobacco products for one year, your premiums can be reduced if you\\nprovide evidence of such and you are approved as a non-smoker by MetLife.</span></i>\",\"order\":13},{\"question\":\"<b><span style=\\\"font-size:10.0pt;line-height:115%;\\nfont-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-font-family:\\nCalibri;mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;\\nmso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;color:#00B0F0;mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:\\nEN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA\\\">How will my premium be billed if I leave the company?</span></b>\",\"answer\":\"<span class=\\\"apple-converted-space\\\"><i><span style=\\\"font-size: 10pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\\\">Should you leave your current employer, you will have the option to take\\nyour policy with you without any change in benefit or rates, including your\\ndiscount. To keep your policy contact The Todd Organization at (888) 640-8470.&nbsp; If the frequency or mode of your payments\\nchange, your premium may be subject to change.</span></i></span>\",\"order\":14},{\"question\":\"<b><span style=\\\"font-size:10.0pt;line-height:115%;\\nfont-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-font-family:\\nCalibri;mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;\\nmso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;color:#00B0F0;mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:\\nEN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA\\\">When do benefits begin following disability?&nbsp;<span class=\\\"apple-converted-space\\\">&nbsp;</span></span></b>\",\"answer\":\"<i><span style=\\\"font-size: 10pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\\\">Benefits begin to accrue after you have been\\ndisabled for 180 days.</span></i>\",\"order\":15},{\"question\":\"<b><span style=\\\"font-siz