ion people live with some form of disability.\n    &lt;br&gt;\n  &lt;/p&gt;\n  \n    &lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;World Health Organization, http://www.who.int/features/factfiles/disability/facts/en/ 2014\n      &lt;br&gt;\n    &lt;/p&gt;\n  \n  &lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;More than 38 million Americans suffer disabling injuries each year.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n\n  &lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;National Safety Council, Injury Facts, 2011 edition.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n\n  \n  &lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;Approximately 1 in 3 people will experience some kind of adult onset disability between the ages of 35 and 65.&lt;/p&gt;\n  &lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;Society for Human Resource Management, Job Accommodation Network Conference, &quot;Plan B&quot; by Steven Nissen, August 2007.&lt;/p&gt;\n  \n  &lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;Almost 3 in 10 workers entering the work force today will become disabled before retirement.&lt;/p&gt;\n  \n    &lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;Social Security Administration, Fact Sheet, January 31, 2007.&lt;/p&gt;\n  \n  \n    &lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;Nearly one in five Americans will become disabled for a year or more before the age of 65.&lt;/p&gt;\n  \n  \n    &lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;Life and Health Insurance Foundation for Education (LIFE), &quot;Disability Insurance: Who Needs It?&quot; May 2007.&lt;/p&gt;\n  \n  &lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;A Medical crisis contributes to half of all mortgage foreclosures.&lt;/p&gt;\n  \n    &lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;Get Sick, Get Out: The Medical Causes of Home Mortgage Foreclosures, Robertson, Egelhof &amp;amp; Hoke\n      &lt;br&gt;\n    &lt;/p&gt;\n  \n  \n  \n    &lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;Disability causes nearly 50% of all mortgage foreclosures, compared to 2% that are caused by loss of life.&lt;/p&gt;\n  \n  \n    &lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;WPLG, Miami, &quot;Disability Insurance Offers Vital Protection,&quot; July 31, 2007.&lt;/p&gt;\n  \n\n&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;Approximately one in three people will experience some kind of adult-onset disability between the ages of 35 and 65, such as arthritis, lupus, diabetes, spinal cord injuries, mental disorders, or MS.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n  &lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;SHRM, Job Accommodation Network Conference &quot;&#39;Plan B&#39; Needed for Adult-Onset Disabilities Such as MS,&quot; speech by Steven Nissen, director of employment programs for the National Multiple Sclerosis Society, August 2007.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n\n  &lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;Since 2000, the number of disabled workers in America has increased by 35% while the financial health of many American workers has declined.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n\n  &lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;Council for Disability Awareness, &quot;Misinformation, Poor Planning Can Threaten Financial Security,&quot; March 7, 2007.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;56 % of U.S. adults surveyed say they would not be able to pay their bills or meet expenses if they became disabled and could not work for a year or longer.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n  &lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;National Association of Insurance Commissioners, &quot;Majority of Americans Unprepared for Financial Impact of Disability,&quot; February 28, 2007.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n\n  &lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;A survey of American workers shows that nine out of 10 workers underestimate their chance of becoming disabled.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n\n  &lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Council for Disability Awareness, &quot;Most Workers Underestimate Chances, Impact of Disability, Survey Shows,&quot; March 7, 2007.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n\n  &lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;Most disabling injuries suffered by American workers occur off the job and are not covered by workers&#39; compensation.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n\n  &lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;National Safety Council, Injury Facts, 2005-2006 edition.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n\n  &lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;The average monthly Social Security Disability Insurance benefit is only $978.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n\n  &lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;Social Security Administration, Fact Sheet, January 31, 2007.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n\n  &lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;About two-thirds of initial applications are denied and the wait for appeals can take as long as three years.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n\n  &lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;The New York Times, &quot;Disability Cases Last Longer as Backlog Rises,&quot; by Erik Eckholm, December 10, 2007.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;!-- autocreated page --&gt;','Fact Sheet',1439818746,30,0,0),(446,187,'error','&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;&gt;There was an error submitting your application.&amp;nbsp; Please contact us at\n&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#6494b4&quot; size=&quot;5&quot;&gt;(888) 640-8470&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br&gt;','Error Submitting Application',1443455370,30,0,0),(447,187,'logout','You have been successfully logged out.','Logged Out',1443455370,30,0,0),(448,187,'about policy','&lt;div&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif&quot; size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;Individual Disability Income (IDI) programs offer individually owned insurance policies offered in a multi-life setting. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: small;&quot;&gt;IDI coverage is offered through a simplified underwriting process (Guaranteed Standard Issue)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: small;&quot;&gt;Level premium structure to your age 67&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: small;&quot;&gt;Policy type is a non-cancellable and guaranteed renewable contract&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: small;&quot;&gt;Coverage is portable (take it with you if you leave the company)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: small;&quot;&gt;Discounted 20% from ‘retail’ rates&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: small;&quot;&gt;Able to cover total compensation over and above the existing Group LTD plan&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: small;&quot;&gt;Since you pay the premiums, benefits would generally be considered non-taxable.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- autocreated page --&gt;','About This Policy',1443455370,30,0,0),(449,187,'about provider','&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 18px; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: 0px 0px; background-repeat: initial;&quot;&gt;MetLife, through its subsidiaries and affiliates, is a global provider of life insurance, annuities, employee benefits and asset management. Serving approximately 100 million customers, MetLife has operations in nearly 50 countries and holds leading market positions in the United States, Japan, Latin America, Asia, Europe and the Middle East.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 18px; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: 0px 0px; background-repeat: initial;&quot;&gt;The MetLife companies provide corporations and individuals with a comprehensive suite of insurance and benefits products and services. We ensure customers’ long-term financial security by matching their needs with the right protection solutions.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 style=&quot;margin: 0px 0px 8px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 15px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: rgb(102, 102, 102); clear: both; line-height: 18px; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: 0px 0px; background-repeat: initial;&quot;&gt;Insurer Financial Strength Ratings&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;table width=&quot;100%&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 18px;&quot;&gt;&lt;tbody&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td valign=&quot;bottom&quot; style=&quot;vertical-align: bottom; text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;h5 style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 13px; vertical-align: baseline; background: 0px 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: 0px 0px;&quot;&gt;A.M. Best Company&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: 0px 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h5&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td valign=&quot;bottom&quot; style=&quot;vertical-align: bottom; text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;h5 style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 13px; vertical-align: baseline; background: 0px 0px;&quot;&gt;Fitch Ratings&lt;/h5&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;h5 style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 13px; vertical-align: baseline; background: 0px 0px;&quot;&gt;Moody&#39;s Investors Service&lt;/h5&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td valign=&quot;bottom&quot; style=&quot;vertical-align: bottom; text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;h5 style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 13px; vertical-align: baseline; background: 0px 0px;&quot;&gt;Standard &amp;amp; Poor&#39;s&lt;/h5&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td nowrap=&quot;nowrap&quot;&gt;American Life Insurance Company&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;Not Rated