></i></span></p>\",\"order\":19},{\"question\":\"<b><span style=\\\"font-size:10.0pt;line-height:115%;\\nfont-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-font-family:\\nCalibri;mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;\\nmso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;color:#00B0F0;mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:\\nEN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA\\\">Are mental disorders covered?&nbsp;<span class=\\\"apple-converted-space\\\">&nbsp;</span></span></b>\",\"answer\":\"<i><span style=\\\"font-size: 10pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\\\">Yes. Disabilities resulting from mental\\ndisorders or substance use disorders are limited to a lifetime benefit of 24\\nmonths. However, this limitation does not apply to any period of time you are\\nconfined to a hospital.</span></i>\",\"order\":20},{\"question\":\"<b><span style=\\\"font-size:10.0pt;line-height:115%;\\nfont-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-font-family:\\nCalibri;mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;\\nmso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;color:#00B0F0;mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:\\nEN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA\\\">What carrier underwrites the program?&nbsp;<span class=\\\"apple-converted-space\\\"></span></span></b>\",\"answer\":\"<p style=\\\"margin-top:2.4pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:27.35pt;\\nmargin-bottom:.0001pt\\\"><span class=\\\"apple-converted-space\\\"><i><span style=\\\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\\\">Metropolitan Life Insurance Company (MetLife\\u00ae) NY, NY, underwrites\\nthe program.<o:p></o:p></span></i></span></p>\",\"order\":21},{\"question\":\"<b><span style=\\\"font-size:10.0pt;line-height:115%;\\nfont-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-font-family:\\nCalibri;mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;\\nmso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;color:#00B0F0;mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:\\nEN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA\\\">Can Metropolitan Life Insurance Company cancel\\nmy policy?&nbsp;<span class=\\\"apple-converted-space\\\">&nbsp;</span></span></b>\",\"answer\":\"<i><span style=\\\"font-size: 10pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\\\">Your policy can never be cancelled or modified\\nwithout your permission, as long as you maintain your premium payments.</span></i>\",\"order\":22},{\"question\":\"<b><span style=\\\"font-size:10.0pt;line-height:115%;\\nfont-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-font-family:\\nCalibri;mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;\\nmso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;color:#00B0F0;mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:\\nEN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA\\\">When is my coverage effective?&nbsp;<span class=\\\"apple-converted-space\\\"></span></span></b>\",\"answer\":\"<span class=\\\"apple-converted-space\\\"><i><span style=\\\"font-size: 10pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\\\">If your application is approved, coverage will become effective as of\\nthe effective date set by the employer and MetLife, regardless of when money is\\npaid to MetLife. &nbsp;Again, for the coverage\\nto be effective, you must have been actively at work for the 90 days prior to\\nand including the date of the application and you must be working at least 30\\nhours per week as of the effective date of the policy.</span></i></span>\",\"order\":23},{\"question\":\"<b><span style=\\\"font-size:10.0pt;line-height:115%;\\nfont-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-font-family:\\nCalibri;mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;\\nmso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;color:#00B0F0;mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:\\nEN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA\\\">What happens if I have not been actively at work\\nfor the entire 90 day period prior to the date of the application?&nbsp;<span class=\\\"apple-converted-space\\\">&nbsp;</span></span></b>\",\"answer\":\"<i><span style=\\\"font-size: 10pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\\\">If you have not been actively at work for the\\nentire 90 day period prior to the date of the application for reasons of\\nhealth, and/or are not actively at work on the day you sign the application,\\nyou may be asked to provide evidence of insurability (proof of good health).</span></i>\",\"order\":24},{\"question\":\"<b><span style=\\\"font-size:10.0pt;line-height:115%;\\nfont-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-font-family:\\nCalibri;mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;\\nmso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;color:#00B0F0;mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:\\nEN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA\\\">What happens if I apply for coverage then decide\\nI don\\u2019t want it?&nbsp;<span class=\\\"apple-converted-space\\\"></span></span></b>\",\"answer\":\"<span class=\\\"apple-converted-space\\\"><i><span style=\\\"font-size: 10pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\\\">If for any reason you are not satisfied with this policy, you may return\\nit within 10 days of its receipt and 100 percent of any premium you have paid\\nwill be refunded, no questions asked, and your policy will be considered never\\nto have been issued. After this time, you may discontinue your individual\\ndisability income coverage anytime you feel that it is no longer creating value\\nor providing protection. However, no premiums will be refunded.</span></i></span>\",\"order\":25},{\"question\":\"<b><span style=\\\"font-size:10.0pt;line-height:115%;\\nfont-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-font-family:\\nCalibri;mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;\\nmso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;color:#00B0F0;mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:\\nEN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA\\\">Who do I call if I have any questions?&nbsp;<span class=\\\"apple-converted-space\\\">&nbsp;</span></span></b>\",\"answer\":\"<i><span style=\\\"font-size: 10pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\\\">If you have any questions or would like help in\\napplying, please contact Hyatt\'s Benefit Consultants at The Todd Organization\\nby dialing (888) 640-8470.</span></i>\",\"order\":26}]','Frequently Asked Questions',1445538837,30,0,0),(460,189,'faq','[{\"question\":\"Whom should I call with questions? \",\"answer\":\"Please call The Todd Organization at (888) 640-8470\",\"order\":0},{\"question\":\"Who pays for this benefit? \",\"answer\":\"Your employer pays the cost of this coverage.\\n\",\"order\":1},{\"question\":\"I already own individual insurance, can I still participate? \",\"answer\":\"Yes. A comparison of the SIP plan with any existing coverage can be illustrated for you by calling (888) 640-8470 for additional information.\\n\",\"order\":2},{\"question\":\"What happens if I terminate employment? \",\"answer\":\"Your coverage is individually owned which means you take it with you if you leave the company.\",\"order\":3},{\"question\":\"If I use tobacco in any form will it affect my premium?\",\"answer\":\"Yes. Your personalized information provides employer-paid premiums for both tobacco and non-tobacco use. Please provide details (type and usage) of your tobacco use after question 4.\",\"order\":4},{\"question\":\"If I don\'t enroll now, can I participate in the future? \",\"answer\":\"If you do not apply for coverage now, you may be required to provide full medical underwriting in the future if you choose to apply later.\",\"order\":5},{\"question\":\"Can I discontinue coverage at any time? \",\"answer\":\"Yes. You may discontinue your participation in this program at any time.\",\"order\":6},{\"question\":\"Can Unum cancel my policy? \",\"answer\":\"Your policy cannot be cancelled or modified before age 65 without your permission..\\n\",\"order\":7},{\"question\":\"Where do I need to send the completed application? \",\"answer\":\"Please complete the application via the web and submit.\\n\",\"order\":8}]','Frequently Asked Questions',1445627068,30,0,0),(451,188,'factsheet','&lt;div&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;5&quot; color=&quot;#6494b4&quot;&gt;Here are the Facts:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot; face=&quot;helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;Worldwide, over one billion people live with some form of disability.&amp;nbsp; Rates of disability are increasing.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;World Health Organization, http://www.who.int/features/factfiles/disability/facts/en/ 2014&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;More than 38 million Americans suffer disabling injuries each year.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;National Safety Council, Injury Facts, 2011 edition.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;Approximately 1 in 3 people will experience some kind of adult onset disability between the ages of 35 and 65.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;Society for Human Resource Management, Job Accommodation Network Conference, &quot;Plan B&quot; by Steven Nissen, August 2007.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;Almost 3 in 10 workers entering the work force today will become disabled before retirement.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;Social Security Administration, Fact Sheet, January 31, 2007.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot; face=&quot;helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;Nearly one in five Americans will become disabled for a year or more before the age of 65.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;Life and Health Insurance Foundation for Education (LIFE), &quot;Disability Insurance: Who Needs It?&quot; May 2007.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;A Medical crisis contributes to half of all mortgage foreclosures.  &lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;Get Sick, Get Out: The Medical Causes of Home Mortgage Foreclosures, Robertson, Egelhof &amp;amp; Hoke&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;Disability causes nearly 50% of all mortgage foreclosures, compared to 2% that are caused by loss of life.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;WPLG, Miami, &quot;Disability Insurance Offers Vital Protection,&quot; July 31, 2007.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;Approximately one in three people will experience some kind of adult-onset disability between the ages of 35 and 65, such as arthritis, lupus, diabetes, spinal cord injuries, mental disorders, or MS.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;SHRM, Job Accommodation Network Conference &quot;&#39;Plan B&#39; Needed for Adult-Onset Disabilities Such as MS,&quot; speech by Steven Nissen, director of employment programs for the National Multiple Sclerosis Society, August 2007.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot; face=&quot;helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;Since 2000, the number of disabled workers in America has increased by 35% while the financial health of many American workers has declined.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;Council for Disability Awareness, &quot;Misinformation, Poor Planning Can Threaten Financial Security,&quot; March 7, 2007.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot; face=&quot;helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;56 % of U.S. adults surveyed say they would not be able to pay their bills or meet expenses if they became disabled and could not work for a year or longer.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;National Association of Insurance Commissioners, &quot;Majority of Americans Unprepared for Financial Impact of Disability,&quot; February 28, 2007.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot; face=&quot;helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;A survey of American workers shows that nine out of 10 workers underestimate their chance of becoming disabled.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Council for Disability Awareness, &quot;Most Workers Underestimate Chances, Impact of Disability, Survey Shows,&quot; March 7, 2007.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot; face=&quot;helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;Most disabling injuries suffered by American workers occur off the job and are not covered by workers&#39; compensation.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;National Safety Council, Injury Facts, 2005-2006 edition.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot; face=&quot;helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;The average monthly Social Security Disability Insurance benefit is only $978.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;Social Security Administration, Fact Sheet, January 31, 2007.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot; face=&quot;helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;About two-thirds of initial applications are denied and the wait for appeals can take as long as three years.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;The New York Times, &quot;Disability Cases Last Longer as Backlog Rises,&quot; by Erik Eckholm, December 10, 2007.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- autocreated page --&gt;','Fact Sheet',1445538837,30,0,0),(452,188,'decline','Do you wish to decline this coverage?&amp;nbsp;&lt;div&gt;Please use the area below to let us know why you are declining.&lt;/div&gt;','Decline',1445538837,30,0,0),(453,188,'contact','&lt;br&gt;','Contact Us',1445538837,30,0,0),(454,188,'apply now','When you click the apply now button you will be transferred to the insurance carrier&#39;s website to complete the simplified enrollment process.&lt;!-- autocreated page --&gt;','Apply Now',1445538837,30,0,0),(455,188,'return from carrier','&lt;!-- autocreated page --&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#6494b4&quot; size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;You application has been submitted successfully!&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;What to expect next...&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;If you have applied for coverage:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Thank you for applying. Your application is currently being reviewed. &amp;nbsp;If we have any questions about your application, we will contact you.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Once your application is approved:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;A policy will be mailed to your home in January.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;If your application is not approved:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;A letter will be sent your home explaining why it was not approved and your rights to appeal that decision.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;If you have declined the opportunity to participate in the Individual Disability Income plan. No further action is necessary. If you later decide to participate in this plan, you will be required to provide proof of good health at that time.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Please contact us at 888-640-8470 with questions.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;','Application Successfully Submitted',1445538837,30,0,0),(456,188,'error','&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;&gt;There was an error submitting your application.&amp;nbsp; Please contact us at\n&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#6494b4&quot; size=&quot;5&quot;&gt;(888) 640-8470&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br&gt;','Error Submitting Application',1445538837,30,0,0),(457,188,'logout','You have been successfully logged out.','Logged Out',1445538837,30,0,0),(458,188,'about policy','&lt;div&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif&quot; size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;Individual Disability Income (IDI) programs offer individually owned insurance policies offered in a multi-life setting. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: small;&quot;&gt;IDI coverage is offered through a simplified underwriting process (Guaranteed Standard Issue)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: small;&quot;&gt;Level premium structure to your age 67&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: small;&quot;&gt;Policy type is a non-cancellable and guaranteed renewable contract&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: small;&quot;&gt;Coverage is portable (take it with you if you leave the company)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: small;&quot;&gt;Discounted 20% from ‘retail’ rates&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: small;&quot;&gt;Able to cover total compensation over 