lity are increasing.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;World Health Organization, http://www.who.int/features/factfiles/disability/facts/en/ 2014&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;More than 38 million Americans suffer disabling injuries each year.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;National Safety Council, Injury Facts, 2011 edition.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;Approximately 1 in 3 people will experience some kind of adult onset disability between the ages of 35 and 65.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;Society for Human Resource Management, Job Accommodation Network Conference, &quot;Plan B&quot; by Steven Nissen, August 2007.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;Almost 3 in 10 workers entering the work force today will become disabled before retirement.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;Social Security Administration, Fact Sheet, January 31, 2007.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot; face=&quot;helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;Nearly one in five Americans will become disabled for a year or more before the age of 65.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;Life and Health Insurance Foundation for Education (LIFE), &quot;Disability Insurance: Who Needs It?&quot; May 2007.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;A Medical crisis contributes to half of all mortgage foreclosures.  &lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;Get Sick, Get Out: The Medical Causes of Home Mortgage Foreclosures, Robertson, Egelhof &amp;amp; Hoke&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;Disability causes nearly 50% of all mortgage foreclosures, compared to 2% that are caused by loss of life.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;WPLG, Miami, &quot;Disability Insurance Offers Vital Protection,&quot; July 31, 2007.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;Approximately one in three people will experience some kind of adult-onset disability between the ages of 35 and 65, such as arthritis, lupus, diabetes, spinal cord injuries, mental disorders, or MS.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;SHRM, Job Accommodation Network Conference &quot;&#39;Plan B&#39; Needed for Adult-Onset Disabilities Such as MS,&quot; speech by Steven Nissen, director of employment programs for the National Multiple Sclerosis Society, August 2007.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot; face=&quot;helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;Since 2000, the number of disabled workers in America has increased by 35% while the financial health of many American workers has declined.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;Council for Disability Awareness, &quot;Misinformation, Poor Planning Can Threaten Financial Security,&quot; March 7, 2007.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot; face=&quot;helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;56 % of U.S. adults surveyed say they would not be able to pay their bills or meet expenses if they became disabled and could not work for a year or longer.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;National Association of Insurance Commissioners, &quot;Majority of Americans Unprepared for Financial Impact of Disability,&quot; February 28, 2007.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot; face=&quot;helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;A survey of American workers shows that nine out of 10 workers underestimate their chance of becoming disabled.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Council for Disability Awareness, &quot;Most Workers Underestimate Chances, Impact of Disability, Survey Shows,&quot; March 7, 2007.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot; face=&quot;helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;Most disabling injuries suffered by American workers occur off the job and are not covered by workers&#39; compensation.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;National Safety Council, Injury Facts, 2005-2006 edition.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot; face=&quot;helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;The average monthly Social Security Disability Insurance benefit is only $978.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;Social Security Administration, Fact Sheet, January 31, 2007.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot; face=&quot;helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;About two-thirds of initial applications are denied and the wait for appeals can take as long as three years.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;The New York Times, &quot;Disability Cases Last Longer as Backlog Rises,&quot; by Erik Eckholm, December 10, 2007.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- autocreated page --&gt;','Fact Sheet',1458235718,30,0,0),(482,191,'decline','Do you wish to decline this coverage?&amp;nbsp;&lt;div&gt;Please use the area below to let us know why you are declining.&lt;/div&gt;','Decline',1458235718