',1463595680,30,0,0),(508,193,'about policy','&lt;div&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif&quot; size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;Individual Disability Insurance (IDI) programs offer individually owned insurance policies offered in a multi-life setting. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif&quot; size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: small;&quot;&gt;IDI coverage is offered through a simplified underwriting process (Guaranteed Standard Issue)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: small;&quot;&gt;Level premium structure to your age 65&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: small;&quot;&gt;Policy type is a non-cancelable and guaranteed renewable contract&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: small;&quot;&gt;Coverage is portable (take it with you if you leave the company)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: small;&quot;&gt;Discounted 30% from ‘retail’ rates&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: small;&quot;&gt;Able to cover total compensation over and above the existing Group LTD plan&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: small;&quot;&gt;Since you pay the premiums, benefits would generally be considered non-taxable.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- autocreated page --&gt;','About This Policy',1463595680,30,0,0),(509,193,'about provider','&lt;div&gt;At Unum, we’re in the business of helping people through difficult \ntimes in their lives. Our financial protection benefits provide \nindividuals and their families with the financial security they need to \nbetter cope with the loss of a loved one or the inability to work due to\n illness or injury.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;We offer a full array of \nbenefits solutions (including education, enrollment services and \nvaluable claim support) to meet the needs of both employers and their \nworkers. And our award-winning absence management and vocational \nrehabilitation services help ease the disruption to both businesses and \nemployers by enabling them to return to full capacity as soon as they \nare able.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;Unum at a glance:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ranks 272 on the Fortune 500&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Protects 20 million people worldwide&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Serves the needs of 175,000 businesses in the U.S. and U.K.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Providing benefits for a third of Fortune 500 companies&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- autocreated page --&gt;','About This Provider',1463595680,30,0,0),(510,194,'faq','[{\"question\":\"What are the main advantages of applying for the coverage through this option rather than attempting to purchase it on my own? \",\"answer\":\"Discounted Premium Rates since you are an employee of  LifePoint Health.&nbsp;<div><br><div>Guaranteed standard issue underwriting allows you to apply for the IDI Plan with no medical exam; however, you will be asked a few medical questions and benefits may be subject to a pre-existing condition limitation.&nbsp;<br></div><div><br></div><div>Convenient payroll deduction.<br></div></div>\",\"order\":0},{\"question\":\"Who pays for this benefit? \",\"answer\":\"You pay for the cost of this coverage through payroll deduction.\\n\",\"order\":1},{\"question\":\"How much coverage can I purchase? \",\"answer\":\"This depends on your income level and any other disability coverage you may have in force.\\n\",\"order\":2},{\"question\":\"I already own individual insurance, can I still participate? \",\"answer\":\"Yes, a comparison of the Supplemental IDI plan with any existing coverage can be illustrated for you by calling Dan Wisted in Atlanta toll-free at (888) 640-8470 or Don Hurwitz in Nashville at (615) 742-8712 or (800) 289-7724 for additional information.\\n\",\"order\":3},{\"question\":\"What happens if I terminate employment? \",\"answer\":\"Your coverage is individually owned which means you take it with you if you leave the company. Your policy premium will not increase until age 65.\",\"order\":4},{\"question\":\"If I use tobacco in any form will it affect my premium?\",\"answer\":\"Yes. Your personalized information provides premiums for both tobacco and non-tobacco use.&nbsp;\",\"order\":5},{\"question\":\"If I don\'t enroll now, can I participate in the future? \",\"answer\":\"If you do not apply for coverage now, you may be required to provide full medical underwriting in the future if you choose to apply later.\",\"order\":6},{\"question\":\"Can I discontinue coverage at any time? \",\"answer\":\"YES. Premiums will be deducted from your pay each pay period. You may discontinue your participation in this program at any time by calling the Unum Policy Services Line at 800-633-7490.\",\"order\":7},{\"question\":\"Can Unum cancel my policy? \",\"answer\":\"Your policy cannot be cancelled or modified before age 65 without your permission, as long as you continue to pay your premiums when due.\\n\",\"order\":8},{\"question\":\"If I become disabled, do I still have to pay premiums? \",\"answer\":\"NO. After 90 days of covered disability, all future premiums will be waived while you continue to receive benefits under the IDI Plan. Any premiums paid during the 90 days will be refunded.\\n\",\"order\":9},{\"question\":\"Where do I need to send the completed application? \",\"answer\":\"Please complete the application via the web and submit.\\n\",\"order\":10},{\"question\":\"Is my IDI benefit payment taxable?\",\"answer\":\"Since you will be paying the premium with after-tax dollars, your benefit, if disabled, will be tax free.\\n\",\"order\":11}]','Frequently Asked Questions',1467077794,30,0,0),(511,194,'factsheet','&lt;div&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;5&quot; color=&quot;#6494b4&quot;&gt;Here are the Facts:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot; face=&quot;helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;Worldwide, over one billion people live with some form of disability.&amp;nbsp; Rates of disability are increasing.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;World Health Organization, http://www.who.int/features/factfiles/disability/facts/en/ 2014&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;More than 38 million Americans suffer disabling injuries each year.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;National Safety Council, Injury Facts, 2011 edition.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;Approximately 1 in 3 people will experience some kind of adult onset disability between the ages of 35 and 65.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;Society for Human Resource Management, Job Accommodation Network Conference, &quot;Plan B&quot; by Steven Nissen, August 2007.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;Almost 3 in 10 workers entering the work force today will become disabled before retirement.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;Social Security Administration, Fact Sheet, January 31, 2007.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot; face=&quot;helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;Nearly one in five Americans will become disabled for a year or more before the age of 65.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;Life and Health Insurance Foundation for Education (LIFE), &quot;Disability Insurance: Who Needs It?&quot; May 2007.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;A Medical crisis contributes to half of all mortgage foreclosures.  &lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;Get Sick, Get Out: The Medical Causes of Home Mortgage Foreclosures, Robertson, Egelhof &amp;amp; Hoke&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;Disability causes nearly 50% of all mortgage foreclosures, compared to 2% that are caused by loss of life.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;WPLG, Miami, &quot;Disability Insurance Offers Vital Protection,&quot; July 31, 2007.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;Approximately one in three people will experience some kind of adult-onset disability between the ages of 35 and 65, such as arthritis, lupus, diabetes, spinal cord injuries, mental disorders, or MS.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;SHRM, Job Accommodation Network Conference &quot;&#39;Plan B&#39; Needed for Adult-Onset Disabilities Such as MS,&quot; speech by Steven Nissen, director of employment programs for the National Multiple Sclerosis Society, August 2007.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot; face=&quot;helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&gt;Since 2000, the number of disabled workers in America has increased by 35% while the financial health of many American workers has declined.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;source&quot;&gt;Council for Disability Awareness, &quot;Misinformation, Poor Planning Can Threaten Financial Security,&quot; March 7, 2007.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot; face=&quot;helvetica, arial, verdana, sans-serif&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;h4&quot;&